sec.p:
The analysis was controlled for rainfall and PM 2.5 (as a proxy for air pollutants), both square root transformed to reduce the impact of extreme values. The analysis was further adjusted for long-term trend (day of study, df = 3), seasonality (day of year, df = 3), day of week, and public holiday. Hospital admission models were additionally adjusted for days under effects of tropical cyclone when warnings are broadcasted for public safety and protection. Partial autocorrelation (PACF) plots and residual plots were used to assess the models and an autocorrelation of AR1 was added. The full formula is as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
